 Port Elizabeth - Walmer police in Port Elizabeth are investigating a case of assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm after an elderly man was brutally assaulted by a person allegedly recklessly riding a quad-bike. "It is alleged that on Friday afternoon, a 67-year-old man confronted a man on a quad-bike for driving recklessly along Sedan Street, Lorraine, Port Elizabeth," said police spokesperson, Capt Sandra Janse Van Rensburg. "The man was severely assaulted and at about 18:45, he went to Walmer police to report the incident. "However, due to his nature of injuries, he needed immediate medical attention." Capt Janse Van Rensburg said that the police have opened a case on behalf of the complainant and a formal statement is yet to be obtained. "The suspect is known and an arrest is imminent." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 